    title: "What Is a Social Media Audit? How to Do One Step by Step in 2026",
    description:
      "Learn how to perform a complete social media audit. Analyze profile optimization, content performance, audience insights, and competitive positioning for growth.",
    difficulty: "intermediate",
    category: "productivity",
    toolSlugs: ["text-cleaner", "excerpt-generator", "url-encoder"],
    relatedContent: ["website-performance-monitoring", "dns-migration-guide", "ssl-certificate-types-comparison"],
    readingTimeMinutes: 12,
    publishedAt: "2026-06-27",
    updatedAt: "2026-07-09",
    author: { name: "Nuvora Team", url: "/about" },
    sections: [
      { heading: "What Is a Social Media Audit and Why Conduct One?", body: "A social media audit is a systematic review of your social media presence across all platforms. It evaluates profile completeness, content performance, audience demographics, engagement metrics, and competitive positioning. Audits reveal what is working, what is not, and where opportunities exist. They should be conducted quarterly for active accounts and annually for passive ones. An audit provides the data foundation for strategy decisions — without it, you are optimizing based on assumptions rather than evidence. Even a 30-minute audit can surface actionable insights." },
      { heading: "Step 1: Profile and Bio Optimization Check", body: "Start by auditing each platform profile for completeness. Check that your profile photo is consistent across platforms, your bio includes relevant keywords, your website link is correct with UTM parameters, and your contact information is up to date. Review your pinned posts — are they still relevant? Check that your handle is consistent or strategically differentiated across platforms. Use our text cleaner to normalize bio text and remove any formatting issues. An optimized profile is the foundation of social media success because it is the first thing potential followers see." },
      { heading: "Step 2: Content Performance Analysis", body: "Analyze your last 30 to 90 days of posts across each platform. Categorize each post by type (image, video, carousel, text, link) and topic theme. Calculate average engagement rate per type — this reveals content formats that resonate most. Identify your top 10 and bottom 10 performing posts. Look for patterns: Do posts with questions get more comments? Do carousels get more saves? Use our excerpt generator to summarize your findings for stakeholder reports. Ranking content objectively prevents emotional attachment to underperforming formats." },
      { heading: "Step 3: Audience and Competitive Analysis", body: "Review your audience demographics on each platform. Are you reaching the right age groups, locations, and professional backgrounds? Compare current data to your target audience profile. Then analyze 3 to 5 competitors or similar accounts. Note their posting frequency, content formats, engagement rates, and follower growth. What gaps exist in their content strategy that you could fill? Our URL encoder with UTM tracking helps measure how much referral traffic each platform sends to your website, providing a direct ROI comparison across channels." },
      { heading: "Step 4: Action Plan and Documentation", body: "Compile your findings into a prioritized action plan. Focus on quick wins first — fixing incomplete profiles, deleting underperforming content, and doubling down on proven content formats. Set specific, measurable goals for the next quarter: increase engagement rate by 20 percent, grow audience by 15 percent, improve click-through rate from bio links by 10 percent. Document your current metrics as a baseline. Schedule the next audit for 90 days from now. A written audit report creates accountability and provides a reference document for strategy decisions." },
    ],
